description:
Trevor Mueller works at an advertising agency by day, and writes comics by night. His latest project is ALBERT THE ALIEN, appearing on Mark Waidâ€™s THRILLBENT site. He has also self-published several other works including JUNKYARD CHASE, THE FAN, and LOS OJOS. And has contributed stories to several anthologies, including READING WITH PICTURES, KILLER QUEEN from Red Stylo Media, and HOPE: THE HERO INITIATIVE from Ronin Studios.

He is also the writer / artist / creator of several award-winning webcomic series (www.trevoramueller.com), and regularly reviews movies, video games, and comics.

Trevor gives lectures and presentations throughout the country at conventions and schools on several topics, including the power of combining creativity and literacy.

Trevor currently lives in Chicago with his wife, Beth, and his cat, Waffles.
name: Trevor Mueller

deck: Illustrator working at Konami best known as the monster designer for the three first games in the Silent Hill series.
description:
Biography

Born in Saitama Japan in 1972 he graduated graphic design in Tama Art University. He began working for Konami in 1997 where he took charge in background and creature designs for the 1st Silent Hill game that was released in 1999. After the game's initial success for re-defining the survival horror genre, he undertook the same responsibilities for the succeeding sequels until the 3rd installment of the series.

He currently works in his home studio as an illustrator and designer. After Team Silent's (The team responsible for Silent Hill in the Former Konami Computer Entertainment Tokyo) dissolution he still contributed his works to the succeeding Silent Hill games developed by Western studios like Silent Hill Origins (2007) and Silent Hill: Homecoming (2008). His most notable contribution to the franchise was his creation of Pyramid Head who became one of the franchises most notable monsters as well as making appearances in the franchise's posters and covers.
name: Masahiro Ito
